# What is a thread?

## An independent path of execution

- One JVM process → **many threads**, each its own instruction sequence
- The OS scheduler multiplexes them across **CPU cores**

## Why bother

- **Latency** — one thread waits on I/O while others keep working
- **Throughput** — spread CPU-bound work across cores

## The catch

- Two threads touching the same memory can **interleave** — the source of most production bugs
- This module: start simple → virtual threads → the hard shared-state cases
